The bail hearing of Enlightened Christian Gathering Church (ECG) leader Shepherd Bushiri, his wife Mary and co-accused Landiwe Ntlokwana continue in the Pretoria Magistrate’s Court. Bushiri and his co-accused spent the weekend in custody at the Kgosi Mampuru Correctional Centre after their bail application was postponed to Monday. They were arrested last week and are facing charges of fraud, money laundering and contravention of the Prevention of Organised Crime Act. The charges relate to a R102 million investment in one of Bushiri’s companies, “Rising Estate.” Shepherd Bushiri and wife’s bail hearing: 